quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  20,133,"And they say, ",footnotes:1:[Is not the Qur’ān an adequate proof of Muḥammad's prophethood and sufficient as a lasting miracle?]
  20,134,"And if We had destroyed them with a punishment before him,{1} they would have said, ",footnotes:1:[Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ).  Also interpreted as "before it," i.e., the Qur’ān.]
  20,135,"Say, ",footnotes:1:[For the outcome of this matter.]
  21,109,"But if they turn away, then say, ",footnotes:1:[The Prophet (ﷺ) made this message known to all people, not concealing any of it from anyone or preferring any group over another.]
  21,110,"Indeed, He knows what is declared of speech, and He knows what you conceal."
  21,111,"And I know not; perhaps it{1} is a trial for you and enjoyment for a time.",footnotes:1:[The postponement of punishment.]
  23,61,"It is those who hasten to good deeds, and they outstrip [others] therein."
  23,62,"And We charge no soul except [with that within] its capacity, and with Us is a record which speaks with truth; and they will not be wronged."
  23,63,"But their hearts are covered with confusion over this, and they have [evil] deeds besides that [i.e., disbelief] which they are doing,"
  24,43,"Do you not see that Allāh drives clouds? Then He brings them together; then He makes them into a mass, and you see the rain emerge from within it. And He sends down from the sky, mountains [of clouds] within which is hail, and He strikes with it whom He wills and averts it from whom He wills. The flash of its lightning almost takes away the eyesight."
  24,44,"Allāh alternates the night and the day. Indeed in that is a lesson for those who have vision."
  24,45,"Allāh has created every [living] creature from water. And of them are those that move on their bellies, and of them are those that walk on two legs, and of them are those that walk on four. Allāh creates what He wills. Indeed, Allāh is over all things competent."
  25,7,"And they say, "
  25,8,"Or [why is not] a treasure presented to him [from heaven], or does he [not] have a garden from which he eats?"
  25,9,"Look how they strike for you comparisons;{1} but they have strayed, so they cannot [find] a way.",footnotes:1:[From their own imaginations in order to deny and discredit you.]
